  <dashboards>
    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Dashboard 1'>
      <style />
      <size maxheight='800' maxwidth='1200' minheight='800' minwidth='1200' preset-index='17' sizing-mode='fixed' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='4' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='98000' id='7' param='horz' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98666' x='667' y='1000'>
            <zone h='98000' id='5' type-v2='layout-basic' w='85333' x='667' y='1000'>
              <zone h='98000' id='3' name='Retention HeatMap' w='41500' x='667' y='1000'>
                <zone-style>
                  <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                  <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                  <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                  <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                </zone-style>
              </zone>
              <zone forceUpdate='true' h='49000' id='10' type-v2='text' w='43833' x='42167' y='50000'>
                <formatted-text>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>The March 2025 cohort retention collapsed from 45% (Month 1) to just 13% (Month 2) — a drop roughly twice as steep as every other cohort. April, which onboarded while the issue was still live, shows the same depressed pattern (42% → 14%).</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Likely Cause</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Timing points to the app update pushed in early March. Cohorts starting before the fix (Jan/Feb) and after it (May/June) both retain 2–3x better at Month 2 than March/April.</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Recommendation</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Audit the March release changelog against a crash/error-rate dashboard for that window. If confirmed, this is a strong argument for a staged-rollout policy on future releases, with automatic retention-anomaly alerts by cohort.</run>
                </formatted-text>
                <zone-style>
                  <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                  <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                  <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                  <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                </zone-style>
              </zone>
              <zone h='49000' id='11' name='Retention Curve' w='43833' x='42167' y='1000'>
                <zone-style>
                  <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                  <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                  <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                  <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                </zone-style>
              </zone>
            </zone>
            <zone fixed-size='160' h='98000' id='6' is-fixed='true' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='13333' x='86000' y='1000'>
              <zone h='18250' id='8' name='Retention HeatMap' pane-specification-id='0' param='[federated.1yzdnw319ru5091buzgm01nzf498].[sum:months_since_signup:qk]' type-v2='size' w='13333' x='86000' y='1000'>
                <zone-style>
                  <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                  <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                  <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                  <format attr='margin' value='4' />
